
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Conan Fitness System

class Person {
  +firstName: String
  +familyName: String
  +birthDate: Date
}

class Trainer {
  +diploma: String
}

class Member {
  +isMember: Boolean
}

class Center {
  +name: String
  +address: String
}

class Room {
  +roomNumber: Integer
  +maxCapacity: Integer
}

class Session {
  +date: Date
  +startTime: Time
  +type: String
}

class GroupSession {
  +trainer: Trainer
}

class IndividualSession {
}

class Participant {
  +person: Person
  +session: Session
}

class Supervisor {
  +trainer: Trainer
  +session: Session
}

class Prospect {
  +isProspect: Boolean
}

class InternTrainer {
  +isIntern: Boolean
}

' Inheritance and associations
Person <|-- Trainer
Person <|-- Member
Person <|-- Prospect
Trainer <|-- InternTrainer

Center "1" *-- "0..*" Room
Room --> Center

Session <|-- GroupSession
Session <|-- IndividualSession

GroupSession "1" --> "1" Trainer
IndividualSession --> "0..1" Trainer

Person "0..*" -- "0..*" Participant
Participant "1" -- "1" Session

Trainer "0..*" -- "0..*" Supervisor
Supervisor "1" -- "1" Session

Center "0..*" -- "0..*" Session
Room "0..*" -- "0..*" Session
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:
- `Person` is a base class for `Trainer`, `Member`, `Prospect`, and `InternTrainer`.
- A `Center` contains multiple `Room`s.
- Each `Room` belongs to exactly one `Center`.
- A `Session` can be either `GroupSession` or `IndividualSession`.
- `GroupSession` must have one `Trainer`.
- `IndividualSession` may not require a `Trainer`.
- `Participant` links a `Person` with a `Session` (a person can participate in multiple sessions).
- `Supervisor` links a `Trainer` with a `GroupSession` (a trainer can supervise multiple group sessions).
- A `Session` can only occur once per room at a given time.
- `Prospect` represents people who are not yet members or participants.
- `InternTrainer` is a subclass of `Trainer` for those not yet supervising sessions.

